.TH "sclp_ftp_cmd" 9 "sclp_ftp_cmd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sclp_ftp_cmd \- executes a HMC related SCLP Diagnose (ET7) FTP command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" sclp_ftp_cmd
.BI "(const struct hmcdrv_ftp_cmdspec *ftp "  ","
.BI "size_t *fsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ftp" 12
pointer to FTP command specification
.IP "fsize" 12
return of file size (or NULL if undesirable)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Attention: Notice that this function is not reentrant - so the caller
must ensure locking.
.SH "RETURN"
number of bytes read/written or a (negative) error code
